## Summary

Closed the code-side gap for T-056b: `session_archiver.py` now has a checkpoint upload mode (`upload_checkpoint`, `plan_checkpoint_upload`, and `--checkpoint-source` / `--checkpoint-slug` / `--checkpoint-timestamp` / `--checkpoint-prefix` / `--public-base-url` / `--checkpoint-content-type` CLI flags). It uploads a single artifact under `cypherclaw/archive/checkpoints/{slug}-{timestamp}/` alongside a `metadata.json` (sha256, size, source filename, upload timestamp, audio/metadata URLs) and prints the constructed `https://cypherclaw.holdenu.com/...` archive URL on stdout.

The live upload itself remains deferred — same dual-blocker as T-056a:
1. The T-056a Opus artifact was never produced (producer cold).
2. R2 credentials aren't in this Darwin lead host's env.

Both are documented in `ESCALATIONS.md` (T-056b) with an exact CLI invocation an operator can run on the CypherClaw box once the producer is up, plus a `--public-base-url` knob if the Worker routes archive objects under a namespaced path.

Validation: `pytest tests/ -x` → 5253 passed, 11 skipped (9 new checkpoint tests in `tests/test_session_archiver.py`); ruff and mypy clean. The pre-existing T-058a hardening test was nudged to set the new checkpoint flags to `None` so its `MagicMock`-built args still flow through the original dry-run branch.

